    "briefMarkdown": "# Multi-Goal Audit: acme/ecommerce-storefront\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThe storefront has strong CMS integration and deployment practices but critical gaps in security, accessibility, and Next.js performance optimization. The specialist passes identified framework-specific issues that the core audit alone would miss.\n\n## Key Findings\n\n- **Critical:** API delivery key bundled into client JavaScript\n- **High:** 40% of product images missing alt text (WCAG 1.1.1 failure)\n- **High:** No ISR for product pages causing degraded TTFB under load\n- **Medium:** Pages Router with no migration path to App Router\n- **Medium:** Skip navigation missing; keyboard users trapped in header nav\n\n## Specialist Insights\n\n### Next.js Specialist\nIdentified ISR gaps, missing middleware for auth redirects, and an opportunity to adopt Server Components for the product listing page (60% reduction in client JS).\n\n### Accessibility Specialist\nFound 12 WCAG 2.1 AA violations across 4 severity levels. Most impactful: missing alt text and insufficient contrast ratios on primary CTAs.\n",
